200	Mathlib provides $\Sheaf.\mathtt{H} \,\colon\, \Sheaf\,J\,\AddCommGrpCat \to \mathbb N \to \mathrm{Type}\,\_$ — an abstract Grothendieck-topology cohomology in $\AddCommGrpCat$. The value category is fixed to $\AddCommGrpCat$; there is no $\ModuleCat k$-flavoured analogue in Mathlib. The iter-009 finding (logged in \texttt{task\_pending.md}) is that closing $\genus C$ honestly as $\dim_k H^1(C, \struct C)$ requires a parallel sheaf cohomology valued in $\ModuleCat k$ rather than $\AddCommGrpCat$, since $\Module.\mathtt{finrank}\,k$ requires a $\Module k$ structure that the $\AddCommGrpCat$-valued $\Sheaf.\mathtt H$ cannot provide.
201	
202	The construction is short. The $\Linear k$-enriched abelian category $\Sheaf(J, \ModuleCat k)$ already has $\HasExt$ (Theorem~\ref{thm:HasExt_Sheaf_Opens_ModuleCatK}), and $\Ext$ groups in any $\Linear k$ abelian category carry a canonical $\Module k$ structure via \lstinline{CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext.instModule}. We mirror $\Sheaf.\mathtt H$'s standard construction $\Ext(\mathtt{constantSheaf}.\mathrm{obj}\,1, F, n)$ with $\AddCommGrpCat$ replaced by $\ModuleCat k$ and the unit object $1$ replaced by $\ModuleCat.\mathrm{of}\,k\,k$.
