262	\label{sec:moduleK_cech}
263	
264	This section opens \emph{Path-2} of Phase~A step~6: the Čech-cohomology approach to Serre finiteness for $H^i(C, \struct C)$ on a smooth proper geometrically irreducible curve. Iter-012 lays the smallest useful sub-step: define the Čech complex of $\toModuleKSheaf C$ for an arbitrary indexed open cover, plus its cohomology object in each degree. Iter-013+ will add the comparison theorem (Čech vs derived-functor cohomology, for an acyclic cover), the affine-finiteness step (each cochain group is a finite-dimensional $k$-vector space when the cover is affine), and the dimension-vanishing step (degree $> 1$ vanishes on a curve); together they will produce the Serre-finiteness instance \lstinline{Module.Finite k (HModule k (toModuleKSheaf C) i)} that downstream \lstinline{smoothOfRelativeDimension_genus} consumes.
265	
266	The carrier on which the iter-013+ work will operate is the Mathlib functor \lstinline{CategoryTheory.cechComplexFunctor} (\texttt{Mathlib/CategoryTheory/Sites/SheafCohomology/Cech.lean}): given a presheaf $F : \Cop \to A$ on a category $C$ with finite products, valued in a preadditive category $A$ with products, and an indexed family $\mathcal U : \iota \to C$, this returns a cochain complex
267	\[
268	  \check C^\bullet(\mathcal U; F) \;:=\; (\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}\,\mathcal U).\mathrm{obj}\,F \;\in\; \mathtt{CochainComplex}(A, \mathbb N).
269	\]
270	For $A = \ModuleCat\,k$, $C = \opens(C.\mathrm{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat})$ (a complete lattice, hence a category with finite products via meets), and $F = (\mathtt{sheafToPresheaf}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\toModuleKSheaf C)$ the underlying presheaf of the iter-006 structure sheaf, the Čech complex is well-defined; its $n$-th cohomology lives in $\ModuleCat\,k$.
271	
272	\begin{definition}[Čech complex of the structure sheaf]
273	  \label{def:Scheme_cechCochain_OC}
274	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.cechCochain_OC}
275	  \uses{def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
276	  Let $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat\,k))$ and $\mathcal U : \iota \to \opens C.\mathrm{left}.\mathtt{toTopCat}$ be an indexed family of opens. Define
277	  \[
278	    \mathtt{cechCochain\_OC}\,(C)(\mathcal U) \;:=\; (\mathtt{cechComplexFunctor}\,\mathcal U).\mathrm{obj}\,\bigl((\mathtt{sheafToPresheaf}\,\_\,\_).\mathrm{obj}\,(\toModuleKSheaf C)\bigr).
279	  \]
280	  This is a cochain complex valued in $\ModuleCat.\{u\}\,k$, indexed by $\mathbb N$.
281	\end{definition}
282	
283	\begin{proof}
284	  \uses{def:Scheme_toModuleKSheaf}
285	  Direct application of Mathlib's \lstinline{cechComplexFunctor}. The required typeclasses (\lstinline{HasProducts (ModuleCat.{u} k)}, \lstinline{HasFiniteProducts (Opens C.left.toTopCat)}, \lstinline{Preadditive (ModuleCat.{u} k)}) are all auto-resolved. The closure body is therefore the one-line term \lstinline{(cechComplexFunctor 𝒰).obj ((sheafToPresheaf _ _).obj (Scheme.toModuleKSheaf C))}; iter-012 plan-agent \lstinline{lean_run_code} probe confirms this typechecks end-to-end against current Mathlib + project state.
286	\end{proof}
