40	  \uses{thm:HasSheafify_Opens_ModuleCatK}
41	  $\ModuleCat k$ is abelian. The sheaf category $\Sheaf(J, A)$ inherits an abelian structure from an abelian $A$ once \lstinline{HasSheafify J A} holds (Theorem~\ref{thm:HasSheafify_Opens_ModuleCatK}). Mathlib's \lstinline{CategoryTheory.HasExt.standard} produces a \lstinline{HasExt} instance from any abelian category. The universe annotation \lstinline{HasExt.\{u+1\}} matches the unique morphism universe of \lstinline{Sheaf (Opens.gT X) (ModuleCat.\{u\} k)}, mirroring the iter-004 $\AddCommGrpCat$ analogue (Theorem~\ref{thm:HasExt_Sheaf_Opens_AddCommGrp}).
