223	\section{The $H^0$ algebraic bridge}
224	\label{sec:HModule_zero}
225	
226	After Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule} the cohomology groups $\HModule\,k\,F\,n$ are well-defined and carry the canonical $\Module k$-structure inherited from \lstinline{Abelian.Ext.instModule}. For Phase~A step~6 (Serre finiteness, deferred), the next algebraic preliminary is the identification of the degree-zero piece $\HModule\,k\,F\,0$ with a Hom group: this is the bridge from sheaf cohomology to representable Hom-functors, and on a connected proper $k$-curve it eventually rewrites $H^0(C, \struct C)$ as $\Gamma(C, \struct C)$ viewed as a $k$-module.
227	
228	The Lean implementation reuses Mathlib's \lstinline{CategoryTheory.Abelian.Ext.linearEquiv₀} (file \lstinline{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/DerivedCategory/Ext/Linear.lean}), which provides
229	\[
230	  \Ext_R(X, Y, 0) \;\simeq_R\; (X \to Y)
231	\]
