451	\label{sec:IsAffineHModuleVanishing_iter040}
452	
453	Iter-038/039 deliver the $H^0$ side of the $\Module\,k$-finite transport: given finiteness of the relevant Hom group, $\HModule^0$ is $\Module\,k$-finite. The cover-evaluation chain on a curve also requires the $H^{>0}$ side, which on an affine open is the geometric statement $H^i(U, F) = 0$ for $i > 0$ (Serre vanishing on affines). Mathlib does not yet provide this for $\ModuleCat\,k$-valued sheaf cohomology, so we package it as a hypothesis: a \texttt{class} that consumers can either receive as an instance argument (when a producer instance is available) or supply explicitly at the call site.
454	
455	\begin{theorem}[Affine cohomology vanishing carrier predicate]
456	  \label{thm:Scheme_IsAffineHModuleVanishing}
457	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IsAffineHModuleVanishing}
458	  \uses{def:Scheme_HModule_prime}
459	  Let $k$ be a field, $C : \Over\,(\Spec\,(\CommRingCat.\mathrm{of}\,k))$, and $F$ a sheaf of $\ModuleCat\,k$ on $\Opens\,(C.\mathtt{left}.\toTopCat)$. The class \lstinline{IsAffineHModuleVanishing k C F} bundles the proposition that for every affine open $U$ of $C.\mathtt{left}$ and every degree $i > 0$, the open-evaluation cohomology $\HModulePrime\,k\,F\,i\,U$ is a subsingleton (equivalently, the zero $k$-module).
460	\end{theorem}
461	
462	\begin{proof}
463	  Definitional: a \texttt{class} with a single field \lstinline{subsingleton_HModule' : \forall \{U\}, IsAffineOpen U \to \forall i, 0 < i \to Subsingleton (HModule' k F i U)}. The choice of \lstinline{Subsingleton} (rather than the categorical \lstinline{Limits.IsZero}) is mandated by the iter-014 typing: $\HModulePrime$ returns a \lstinline{Type u} (the underlying type of an $\Ext$ group) rather than a \lstinline{ModuleCat} object, so categorical \lstinline{IsZero} does not directly apply. The two formulations are nevertheless equivalent via Mathlib's \lstinline{ModuleCat.subsingleton_of_isZero}; the \lstinline{Subsingleton} formulation chosen here is more directly chainable into \lstinline{Module.Finite} via instance synthesis (see Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_module_finite_HModule_prime_of_isAffineHModuleVanishing}).
464	\end{proof}
