617	\section{Stein finiteness of global sections (iter-044)}
618	\label{sec:module_finite_globalSections_iter044}
619	
620	Iter-043 introduced the wholespace H${}^0$ Hom-finiteness carrier predicate \lstinline{IsHModuleHomFinite} (Theorem~\ref{thm:Scheme_IsHModuleHomFinite}) and noted that its producer instance for $F = \toModuleKSheaf\,C$ on a proper geometrically connected $k$-curve $C$ would follow from Stein factorization $\Gamma(C, \struct C) = k$. Iter-044 lays the geometric groundwork: the algebraic input \lstinline{Module.Finite k (Γ(C.left, ⊤))} that the carrier-instance producer (iter-045+) consumes.
621	
622	The result follows directly from Mathlib's \lstinline{AlgebraicGeometry.finite_appTop_of_universallyClosed} (\lstinline{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Morphisms.Proper}): for $X$ integral, $f \colon X \to \Spec K$ universally closed and locally of finite type, the structure-morphism ring map $f.\mathtt{appTop} \colon K \to \Gamma(X, \struct X)$ is module-finite. Both \lstinline{UniversallyClosed} and \lstinline{LocallyOfFiniteType} follow from \lstinline{IsProper f}; integrality is assumed as a separate hypothesis (it is the natural structural input here, in line with Stein's theorem; the \lstinline{GeometricallyIntegral} variant yields it via \lstinline{isIntegral_of_subsingleton} on the singleton $\Spec K$, but that derivation is left to the consumer).
623	
624	The bridging from $\mathtt{RingHom.Finite}$ to $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}$ uses two ingredients:
625	\begin{itemize}
626	  \item \lstinline{RingHom.finite_algebraMap}: $(\mathtt{algebraMap}\,A\,B).\mathrm{Finite} \iff \Module.\mathrm{Finite}\,A\,B$ when $B$ has the algebra structure $\mathtt{RingHom.toAlgebra}\,f$.
627	  \item \lstinline{Module.Finite.of_equiv_equiv}: transport $\Module.\mathrm{Finite}$-ness across a ring iso on the base ring (here $\mathtt{\Gamma\!Spec\!Iso}\,(\CommRingCat.\mathrm{of}\,k) \colon \Gamma(\Spec k, \top) \cong k$) given the algebra-map compatibility.
628	\end{itemize}
629	
630	The iter-006 algebra structure on $\Gamma(C.\mathtt{left}, U)$ is via \lstinline{kToSection C U} (Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_kToSection}), which factors as $(\mathtt{\Gamma\!Spec\!Iso}\,k)^{-1} \circ C.\mathtt{hom}.\mathtt{appTop} \circ \rho$ where $\rho$ is the trivial restriction $\top \to U$ for $U = \top$ (i.e. $\rho = \mathtt{id}$, collapsed via \lstinline{Subsingleton.elim} on the $\top \to \top$ hom-set). The proof body therefore matches the algebra-map compatibility under \lstinline{Module.Finite.of_equiv_equiv}.
