630	\subsection{Use in Serre finiteness}
631	
632	For a proper geometrically integral $k$-curve $C$ a $2$-affine cover with affine intersection always exists (e.g.\ remove a closed point to get one affine, remove another to get the second; their intersection is the curve minus two points, again affine on a $k$-curve). The bundle $C.\AffineCoverMVSquare$ then feeds the iter-029+ Serre-finiteness chain:
