213	  \label{def:Scheme_cechCohomology_OC}
214	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.cechCohomology_OC}
215	  \uses{def:Scheme_cechCochain_OC}
216	  With $(C, \mathcal U)$ as in Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_cechCochain_OC}, define the $n$-th \v{C}ech cohomology to be the $n$-th homology of the \v{C}ech cochain complex. The result lives in the category of $k$-modules.
